  "prompt": "Can I deactivate my Roku device?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deactivate or deregister your Roku device from your account. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Using the Roku Device**:\n   - Go to the home screen on your Roku device.\n   - Navigate to \"Settings.\"\n   - Select \"System.\"\n   - Choose \"Advanced system settings.\"\n   - Select \"Factory reset.\"\n   - Follow the prompts to reset your device.\n\nThis will unlink it from your account, but it will also erase all your preferences, settings, and channels.\n\n2. **Using the Roku Website**:\n   - Go to the Roku website and log into your Roku account.\n   - Select \"Manage Devices\" from the account settings.\n   - Find the device you wish to deactivate and select it.\n   - Follow the prompts to remove it from your account.\n\nKeep in mind that deactivating or resetting the device will erase all personal data, so make sure you have backed up any important information.",
